title: For Sale:  CZ 40B-40cal
postcontent:
The CZ 40B began life in approx. 2001 as a joint venture between Colt and CZ.  The gun is a dedicated built-from-the-ground-up .40 caliber - not an adaptation of a 9mm frame. They made it with an alloy frame, a double stack clone of the 1911 grip frame style, and the Sig-style locking system. It's only commonality with the CZ 75/85 series pistols lies in the use of the CZ 75/85 double/single action trigger, the CZ 75/85 sear blocking safety, and the CZ 75B magazines.
Colts bankruptcy put an end to this deal so CZ replaced the trigger in what was going to be the Colt Z40, made some other changes and sold them out through a few distributors. 
I have need of thinning my collection so this sorta rare CZ gets the axe. It has approximately 400 rounds through it. All were handloads and I had zero failures. It will come with a box, 2 mags and the loader.
I would prefer cash but............................
I will not deliver and I will sell only to Ohio residents with proper ID.
More scans are available, just request.
